        <p> {{ page.overview.intro|raw }} Times Square. On the way there, however, we stopped at Applebee's and treated ourselves to breakfast. </p>
        <p> Freshly fortified, we then boarded the bus and wound our way through Manhattan. Here we noted several points that we wanted to visit again later. Although the bus drove really slowly and made very little progress, it was so cold that we got out near our hotel and got a hot chocolate. Since we just couldn't get warm, we decided to go to our room. However, we first bought an NYPD coat for our neighbor's dog Skippy, as requested. </p>
        <p> After spending some time in the room, we noticed that the last Brooklyn bus should be leaving soon, so we set out again. We just caught the bus, and even though we were now wearing more clothes, it remained terribly cold. To Brooklyn, we didn't go over the Brooklyn Bridge, but over the Manhattan Bridge instead, which gave us a good view of the neighboring bridge for photos. </p>
        <p> At the last stop in Brooklyn, we left the bus, took the subway one station, and then arrived at our target food market. Basti got a fried mozzarella pocket from the Italian vendor, while I got Afghan rice with chicken and a much too spicy sauce. </p>

