        <p> Then we briefly strolled into the shopping center next door, where I also found some pants. </p>
        <p> Back on the subway, we headed to the Union Square Holiday Market. It's like a Christmas market like we have at home, just not as crowded and less focused on Christmas. With a detour via a drugstore, we continued to Madison Square Park. There should have been a large, real gingerbread house here. However, we found nothing except grass and a lonely Christmas tree. Basti then checked online again and discovered that the house was only there until the 19th. Darn! </p>
        <p> By this time we were so exhausted again that we started making our way back to the hotel, got something to drink on the way, and fell into bed. </p>
